properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 13 at 5:37AM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant HIll MO
properties.description:
...Dangerously Cold Wind Chills Through Thursday Morning...

A strong cold front has pushed through the region. Behind this
front, strong northwest winds and dangerously cold wind chills
have developed and spread across the region through the morning.

* WHAT...Very cold wind chills. Wind chills as low as 15 below
zero.

* WHERE...In Kansas, Wyandotte and Johnson KS Counties. In
Missouri, Jackson County.

* WHEN...Until noon CST today.

* IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY
